messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Hi, I am, you know, there's an emergency.
Okay, ma'am, what's your location?
Yes, I am on Hough Road.
I am in water, and it's taken me away.
Okay, ma'am, we're on the way. You're at Hough Road and where?
I'm right in the middle of Hough Road.
What's the nearest crossway, do you think?
Summit Estates Drive.
Okay, stay on the line. What's your name?
Erica Strickland.
Okay, Erica. Help is on the way.
Please, hurry, ma'am.
Are you the only one in the car?
Yes, and my car's starting to flood.
Okay, all right. They're on the way. Please try to remain calm.
Ma'am, it's coming in quick!
No, they're on the way, Erica. Stay calm.
What do I need to do, ma'am?
Right now, you can't do much. Your car died, correct?
Yes, ma'am.
Okay. Is there anybody else around?
No, nobody.
All right. What color is your vehicle?
It's gray.
Okay. Stay on the line.
Can I try and get out and get on my roof?
No, stay in the car. We're getting help. Please stay on the line, Erica.
Please hurry.
Erica, you're not going to go into the water, okay?
But it's coming in fast.
Do not go into the water.
Are they coming, ma'am?
Yes, they are. I know it seems like a long time, but just try to stay calm.
Are they going to be able to help me?
Yes, they will. Just hang in there.
I was trying to get home. My husband's been in the hospital all night. I was getting his prescription.
Just stay with me, Erica. It's just you in the car, right?
Yes, ma'am. Please hurry.
Listen, don't get out of the vehicle and don't go into the water, okay?
Okay.
Stay on the line with me. I'm here with you.
I'm sorry.
You're not going to die, ma'am. Stay in the car.
How are they going to get to me if the road is flooded?
They have all kinds of ways to get to you, okay?
Are you sure I can't get out and get on my roof?
No, stay calm, okay?
Yes, ma'am.
Erica, I want you to release your seatbelt if you have it on.
Okay.
And unlock your door. Do not open the door, okay?
Okay.
Erica, it's the sheriff's department. Are you on the north or the south side of Summit Estates, do you know?
I'm right in the middle, right where you go over the little bridge. Please, hurry.
They're on the way, okay?
Okay.
You need to tell me if the water reaches the bottom of your window.
It's at my hood, but it's coming up fast.
Let me know if the water reaches your window, okay?
Okay.
Stay on the line.
Please talk to me.
I'm here, Erica. I'm here.
My husband was in the hospital last night, and I was getting a prescription.
Okay, and you had passed through there before and were coming back?
Yes, I had to get his prescription. He was in bad pain.
Have you called him or did you just call us?
No, I called you right away.
Good, good. Just hang in there, okay?
Are they on the way?
Yes, they've been on the way.
Where's the water now?
Just relax. They're coming, okay?
Please just tell them to hurry.
They are. Hang in there.
I just don't want to drown.
That's not going to happen. Stay with me.
How are they going to get to me if the road is flooded?
They have ways, Erica. Trust us.
Please just tell them to hurry, please.
They are hurrying. I promise.
Okay.
Erica, I want you to release your seatbelt, if you haven't already.
It's off, ma'am.
Okay, all right. Unlock your door, but do not open it.
Okay.
Is the water up to your window?
It's at my hood but not at my window yet.
Okay, let me know if it gets higher.
Okay. I'm scared.
I know, but they're coming.
What should I do now?
Just stay calm and hold on, Erica.
Yes, ma'am. Please hurry.
I'm here with you. Don't worry.
I'm holding on. I just don't want to drown.
You're not going to drown. We're here with you. Help is coming.
Thank you.
You're welcome. I'm here with you.
It's coming in faster. I can see it.
Stay calm, Erica. As hard as it is, stay calm.
How long will they take?
They should be there soon. Just hang on.
Are they talking to you?
Yes, they say they can see you. Just hang on.
What should I do if the water gets higher?
If the water reaches your window, let me know immediately, okay?
Okay.
Are you wearing a seatbelt?
No, I took it off.
Good. Keep the door unlocked but closed.
Okay.
Erica, are you still with me?
Yes, ma'am.
Good, just hang on.
Okay, I'll try.
You're doing great.
Thank you.
Stay on the line with me.
Yes, ma'am.
They're coming to get you.
I see them!
Good! Help is there. Hang on, they'll get you out.
Thank you so much.
You're welcome. Stay safe and listen to their directions.
Yes, ma'am. Thank you.
